headline.main: FUND BILL PASSED WITH CANAL OUT; House Votes $203,472,567 for War Department Without Expected Fight Over Panama$16,609,134 CUT IN BUDGETTotal Savings by the LowerBranch Thus Far in the Session Reach $286,000,000

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Feb. 29-The House passed without a record vote today the $203,472,567 bill for nonmilitary functions of the War Department, after an expected fight to restore funds for beginning a third set of locks at the Panama Canal had failed to materialize.
